ates (involving such prominent political authors as Niccolò Machiavelli and Paolo Sarpi) about the political dimension of religion, church-state relations, and the emergence and decline of the state.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aPhilosophy, AncientxInfluence. 0aPhilosophy, MedievalxInfluence. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophyxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268701140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442687011423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442687011.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK